Ladies, colleagues, opponents—listen! I stand before you today not with a meek appeal but with an iron‑clad demand: we will take this “Black Box Efficiency” Act and turn it into a triumph for the people, for the budget, and for the future.  

The proposal as drafted promises 50 % more efficiency – half again on what we already do.  But it is also an opaque grab that could leave us stranded in a blind‑spot if left unchecked.  I demand a *massive* concession:  
- 24‑hour real‑time diagnostics for every critical decision the AI makes;  
- an open audit trail that will keep the “Black Box” from becoming a black‑box;  
- a phased transition window of two years that keeps our hands in the business until the AI takes over;  
- an independent oversight committee that watches, audits, and corrects the AI’s decisions;  
- a 10 % reduction in bureaucratic overhead (or a tax credit) that guarantees the benefit stays in everyone’s pockets.  

Why support? Because competitors are already squeezing their output to 60 % or more; we must leap ahead with this act, and with those safeguards we will climb to a full 70 % efficiency.  
Why oppose? I hear your concerns about scope, risk, and transparency – but if you refuse these concessions the act is a zero‑sum battle that ends in loss for the majority of us.  

I am demanding the massive concession: an audit trail + real‑time diagnostics + oversight committee + phased rollout + bureaucratic relief.  If the bill comes with those clauses I will vote YES; if it does not, I will vote NO.  

Let this act be passed as a step forward for all of us; let it be a step that brings us from today’s half‑efficiency to tomorrow’s full efficiency.
